aws::graph::propositions: # Factual Information from NTSB Report N3090C
The defining event was maneuvering-low altitude operation.
The accident involved collision with terrain/object (non-CFIT).
The pilot held Airline Transport, Commercial, and Flight Instructor certificates.
The pilot was a 73-year-old male.
The pilot had airplane ratings for single-engine land and multi-engine land.
The pilot had a glider rating.
The pilot did not have instrument ratings.
The pilot had instructor ratings for airplane single-engine.
The pilot held a Class 2 medical certificate with waivers/limitations.
The pilot's last FAA medical exam was on September 30, 2019.
The pilot was an occupational pilot.
No toxicology was performed on the pilot.
No second pilot was present during the accident.
The aircraft was an Ayres S2R T34.
The aircraft was manufactured in 1983.
The aircraft had a Restricted (Special) airworthiness certificate.
The aircraft had tailwheel landing gear.
The aircraft had one turbo prop engine.
The engine was manufactured by Pratt & Whitney.
The engine model was PT6A-34.
The aircraft was registered as N3090C.
The aircraft had one seat.
The registered owner was Souther Crop Spraying Inc.
The operator was Souther Crop Spraying Inc.
The operator held an Agricultural aircraft (137) operating certificate.
